================================================================================
Third-Party Content
================================================================================

This product optionally ingests content from third-party sources at runtime.
Attribution and license terms for each external content source are tracked in
docs/compliance/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md and in LICENSES/.

When the `SPARC_AWS_LABS_CDEF_ENABLED=true` runtime flag is set, SPARC fetches
OSCAL Component Definitions from:

  awslabs/oscal-content-for-aws-services
  https://github.com/awslabs/oscal-content-for-aws-services
  Copyright Amazon.com, Inc. or its affiliates.
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
  See LICENSES/AWS-LABS-OSCAL-CONTENT-LICENSE for the full license text.

Ingested Component Definitions retain the upstream license and are flagged in
SPARC with `import_metadata.source_type = "aws_labs"`. Users who modify these
definitions must do so via the in-app "Copy for editing" workflow, which
preserves the original under its upstream license and creates an editable
derivative.
